      "type": "string",
      "content": "two equal and opposite charges separated by a distance"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>An electric dipole consists of two equal and opposite charges (±q) separated by distance (d). Its dipole moment is:</p> \\[ \\vec{p} = q\\vec{d} \\] <p>where \\(\\vec{d}\\) points from negative to positive charge.</p>"
    },
